  You might be able to increase the amount of [basic State Pension](/state-pension) to <%= lower_basic_state_pension_rate %> per week if:

  - your spouse or civil partner made enough National Insurance contributions before 6 April 2016
  - your spouse or civil partner was born on or after 6 April 1950 (this rule doesn’t apply to you if you’re a woman married to a man)

  One of the following must also apply:

  - you don’t qualify for any basic State Pension
  - your basic State pension is less than <%= lower_basic_state_pension_rate %> per week

  You’ll get the increase when either you or your spouse or civil partner reach [State Pension age](/state-pension-age), whichever is later.

  ##If you become widowed or your civil partner dies

  You may be able to increase your [basic State Pension](/state-pension) up to <%= higher_basic_state_pension_rate %> a week if:

  - your own basic State Pension is less than <%= higher_basic_state_pension_rate %> a week
  - your late spouse or civil partner made enough National Insurance contributions before 6 April 2016

  You may also inherit a portion of their [Additional State Pension](/additional-state-pension).

  ^You won’t be able to increase your basic State Pension or inherit any Additional State Pension if you remarry or form a new civil partnership before you reach State Pension age.^

  You also might be eligible for [Widowed Parent’s Allowance](/widowed-parents-allowance), a [Bereavement payment](/bereavement-payment) or [Bereavement Allowance](/bereavement-allowance) if you haven’t reached State Pension age.

  ##If you divorce your spouse or civil partner

  You may be able to increase your [basic State Pension](/state-pension) up to <%= higher_basic_state_pension_rate %> a week if:

  - your own basic State Pension is less than <%= higher_basic_state_pension_rate %> a week
  - your divorced spouse or civil partner had enough National Insurance contributions before 6 April 2016

  ^You won’t get the increase if you remarry or form a new civil partnership before you reach State Pension age.^

